'''Ulikuo gemstones''' were found only on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Kip]].<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|III|278|ulikuo stones}}</ref> Their cultural significance warranted unauthorized mining a crime punishable by lifetime imprisonment. In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], [[Zorba Desilijic Tiure]] was convicted on charges of illegal removal of ulikuo stones, and sentenced to 45 standard years in prison. [[Gorga Desilijic Aarrpo/Legends|Gorga Desilijic Aarrpo]] also ran a profitable black-market trade in these gems on Kip with a silent partner. Traditionally, [[Tapani]] nobles presented ulikuo gemstones to each other as part of a marriage proposal.

